ra begins with, &quot;And say, &quot;Praise to Allah..&quot;[17:111] - and then Surah al-Kahf begins with &quot;[All] praise is [due] to Allah, who has sent down upon His Servant the Book...&quot; [18:1] - The begining of this Surah is an enactement from the instruction to say, Alhamdulillah from the last Ayat of the previous Surah. About Surah Al-Kahf: Surah Al-Kahf is the Makki Surah and is the 18th Surah of the Holy Quran. Al-Kahf - سورة الكهف - ( The Cave ) - Read Quran القران الكريم in English translation by Mohsin Khan - SearchTruth . Other scholars believe that Ayat 3 of Surah Al-Ma&#x27;idah is the last revealed by Prophet Muhammad (PBUH). Upon the guidance of God, they fled the city where believers were persecuted, together with their dog , and took refuge in a cave where they fell asleep. The tafsir of Surah Kahf verse 11 by Ibn Kathir is unavailable here. It came between the 8th and 10th year of Prophethood. Surah Al Kahf (The Cave) Ayat 75. It states that when humans go back to Allah, every soul repays the debt of the sins they committed and earn rewards from Allah. Tafheem ul Quran Surah 18 Al-Kahf Ayat [Rukuh]: 1-12 [1], 13-17 [2], 18-22 [3], 23-31 [4], 32-44 [5], 45-49 [6], 50-53 [7], 54-59 [8], 60-70 [9], 71-82 [10], 83-101 [11], 102-110 [12] Ayat Themes of Surah 18. This book Tafsir Surah Al-Kahf is the English translation of the commentary on this blessed surah in an easy to read manner verse-by-verse by the renowned Saudi scholar Allamah Muhammad bin Sal (He has made it) Straight to give a warning (to the disbelievers) of a severe punishment from Him, and to give glad tidings to the believers (in the Oneness of Allah Islamic Monotheism), who work righteous deeds, that they shall have a fair reward (i.e. Visit alim.org today to view the Surah 18. It includes four historical stories, which we can derive amazing lessons from. Surat al-Kahf, the Quranic chapter named after the young companions of the cave, has been noted by scholars for its unique vir